VAR stranger_opened = false
~ stranger_opened = true
The stranger doesn't melt back into the crowd this time. They look at you like a debt that grew teeth. "You weren't supposed to last a week. Pull a name off the street, point it at Varga, walk away — that was the job." A long pause. "But you went and got *interesting*. So now you want to know who you were before Ashfall ate the rest." They almost smile. "It'll cost you. Everything worth knowing does."
* [Who am I?]
    "Not here. Not for free. Press me, or pay me — your call. But know that some doors don't close behind you."
    -> END
* [Who sent you?]
    "Wrong question. The right one is who paid to make you forget. Ask me that properly and we'll talk."
    -> END
